        <div n="578-451O" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Copied from Swift <lb/> by mr Will <lb/> Collins the Poet</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-1"> With a whirl of thought opprest&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-2"> I sunk from Reverie to Rest</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-3"> a Horrid Vision seiz'd my head</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-4"> I saw the Graves yawn up their Dead</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-5"> Iove arm'd with terrors burst the skies</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-6"> and Thunder roars, and Lightning flies</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-7"> amaz'd confus'd it's fate unknown</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-8"> The World stood trembling round his throne</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-9"> While Each Pale Sinner hung his head</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-10"> Iove Nodding shook the heavns and said</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-11"> `Offending Race of human kind</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-12"> `By Nature Custom Learning blind</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-13"> `You who thro frailty stepd aside</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-14"> `and You who never err'd thro Pride</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-15"> `and You whom Diffrent Sects have sham'd</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-16"> `and come to see each other Damn'd</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-17"> `So some Folks told you, but they knew,</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-18"> `no more of Iove's designs than You<gap/><gap/></l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-19"> `I to such Blockheads set my Wit</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-578-451O-line-20"> `I damn such Fools! Go Go, you're bit────578-451O   </l></lg></div>
